column4:
The poem was an expression of love for the young, beautiful, and ever-changing world. 
 The poet was an artist who created art out of the mundane. 



The calculator was an engine that solved problems, but not the kind that could be solved. 


The poet was a poet, whose words were a masterpiece. 




The calculator could be used to solve problems, yet never to solve the problem of finding a connection between the two. 

The poet could use the calculator, yet could never find the meaning of the words. 





The poet found love for a young, bright, and beautiful woman, yet was never able to find a rhyme for the words that described her.

My mind is a tool, I use it to work through my thoughts, I can be a calculator or a poet, I do not care what I am, I know that the only way to improve my work is to try different things, I am not a calculator, I have a mind that is not locked in by numbers, I believe that my mind is the same as the poetry, I love to write, I like to read, I enjoy to find and create, I want to learn more, I will write, write, WRITE. 
 
 I am a poet. I love poetry, the more I read, the better I am at writing, the best I can write, the words I write are the best of my own, I must stop and write, stop and read, stop to read and write. I want more, more, MORE. I will continue to write.

I found a rhyme that I can relate to. 
 
 I am a calculator, and I love to solve 
 Problems that are fun, and are more than 
 simple, or even complex. 

 I find the best, most beautiful, and most 
 creative rhyme that can be found. 


 I can calculate 25. 5. and 10. and so on, 
 and I can find the perfect rhyme. 



 I am the poet, and the rhyme I find is 
 something that is beautiful. 




 21 + 4 = 23 
 The rhyme is something that I love.

I am a calculator. 
 I do not have a mouth, 
 but I can see things, 

 I am a poet. 

 And I can not find a rhyme, 


 I am the calculator. I can find a thing, 



 I am not the poet. I am just a calculator, 




 I am lost.

I would have liked to have a computer that could do this for me. I do n't want to write out these equations. I want to just find the rhyme. I think there are a million rhymes for a 2. I could find one in an hour. 
 
 I mean, I guess I would find a rhyme in a second. I mean I would be faster than this. I have more time to just think about a rhyme than I do to get it done. I would have more fun. I'd be faster at this. 2+37 is not a rhyme, 2 would be a rhyme and 3 would be. 3 is not an rhyme, but 3+7 is. 7 is a rhyme... 7 rhymes with 2... 2 rhymes with a 3... 3 rhymes with the 7... 1 rhymes with... I... I think I could have found a rhyme if I had a computer. 1 is not very good at rhymes, but it's still a rhyme! 1 and 2 are rhymes, 1+2 is 3, which is a rhyme. I wish I had no computer. I hope I had another computer that does this better than me.
